# triggerdelay: manual worked example 3 -- clocked mode. Patching `clock` makes
# `delay` relative to one clock cycle; the default delay 1.0 means "one clock
# cycle". The clock period is learned from consecutive rising edges (like delay),
# so it is only known after the second edge.
#
# clock (I2): rising edges t0, t20, t40 -> period learned = 20 ticks (known @t20)
# input (I1): rising edge t25 (after the period is known), gate length 1 tick.
#   delay = 1 cycle = 20 ticks -> output rises t45.
# In clocked mode the *gate length* is still the input's own length (1 tick,
# real time) unless gatelength is patched.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[triggerdelay]
    input  = I1
    output = O1
    clock  = I2
>>>
@0 set I2 1
@1 set I2 0
@20 set I2 1
@21 set I2 0
@25 set I1 1
@26 set I1 0
@40 set I2 1
@41 set I2 0
@44 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
@45 expect O1 1 tol 1e-4
@46 expect O1 0 tol 1e-4
